Taney County issues warning on outbreak of 5th disease
------------------------------------------------
The Taney County Health Department warns people to be aware of area cases of 5th disease, a contagious viral illness. Kim Foster, the Taney County Health Department epidemiologist, said there have been 32 cases. The disease has symptoms of the common cold: fever, runny nose and headache.

"5th disease is usually mild and will go away on its own," Foster said. "However, it is very contagious."

Mike Brothers, a spokesman for the Springfield-Greene County Health Department, said he didn't know of any cases of 5th disease in Greene County.

[Byline: Sarah Okeson]

